rComments: had socknat for protest and pop culture. Very caring, kind, and lenient with assignments. Very knowledgeable.

Professor Socknat is a great lecturer who really cares about his students. His passion for what he teaches makes his class fascinating and enjoyable. I am so lucky to have Professor Socknat as my lecturer.

Super nice older fella, very accessible outside of class and is kind to his students. Played a lot of videos in our class and students simply stopped showing up, however, I still found the course very interesting. An easy grader and had a lot of fun little projects in our class - like a high school course! Highly recommend him if you get the chance
Very helpful. Great sense of humor. Professional and great as a prof!
Amazing and better then good!

I can't say enough good things about Professor Socknat. He is a wonderful prof, excellent orator, extremely knowledgable when it comes to Canadian history, and despite the comment above, he is well informed about Quebec history too. I think most of all, he clearly cares about what he is doing. I cannot recommend him enough.
Incredibly helpful, approachable, friendly. He obviously loves what he teaches. If you take the ABP at St. George Campus you want to be in his class.
